macro.title: Powell sends mortgage rates higher as he questions December cut
macro.what: Mortgage rates rose by 14 basis points after the Fed cut rates, as Powell's hawkish tone pushed back on December rate cut expectations.
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.
